<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-948-300  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 948 300.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  Dec 4 1989 v217 n24 p38(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Can telcos ACD? (automatic call distribution)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wilson, Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>There is a boom in the market for automatic all distributiontechnology.andP;  Telemarketing, price reductions in technology andincreasing labor costs, have pushed the high volume service to newheights.andP;  Fortunately for Local Exchange Carriers, automatic calldistribution equipment for central offices has been convenientlyenhanced.andP;  ACD technology can work as either a central officebased system , as a complement to Centrex services or as astand-alone.andP;  The service is being offered by most Regional BellHolding companies, but the ability of the companies to effectivelyserve the market has come into question.andP;  Some analysts questionwhether the local companies have the expertise to handle thecomplex technology.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Automatic Call DistributorsTechnologyTelephone CompaniesSupport ServicesMarket Penetration.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>